name: furaneol

Phenyl groups, when connected to a furan ring, tend to increase the melting point due to the enhancement of the crystalline structure and the increase in molecular weight. In the case of furaneol, we have two additional phenyl rings linked in a linear fashion, which would notably augment the melting point. Each additional phenyl group can be estimated to add approximately 100°C to the melting point due to increased pi-pi interactions, rigidity, and molecular weight.
